# Playwright tests (`*.playwright.test.ts` / `*.playwright.spec.ts`)

JSDoc above tests and line comments in these files: follow AGENTS.md code-comment rules (plain text, no Markdown bold/italic; single quotes instead of grave accents for inline references).

## Preconditions

- Run against a **production Electron build** after relevant source changes (`yarn quasar:build:electron` / `quasar build -m electron`). See [README.md](README.md).
- [playwright.config.ts](playwright.config.ts): `workers: 1`, `fullyParallel: false`, unified `outputDir` `test-results/playwright-artifacts`, and `testMatch` covering `src/components/**` and `e2e-tests/**` Playwright files. Terminal reporter: `line` (concise progress; no per-pass list spam; failures in full), plus HTML report `test-results/playwright-report` (sibling folder to avoid reporter vs artifact path overlap).
- Storybook VRT: [`.storybook-workspace/playwright.storybook-visual.config.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/playwright.storybook-visual.config.ts) uses the same **`line`** reporter pattern and HTML under **`test-results/storybook-visual-*`**. Per-story **`[storybook-visual]`** console progress is off unless **`FA_STORYBOOK_VISUAL_VERBOSE=1`** (see [storybook-stories.mdc](storybook-stories.mdc) and [`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts)).

## Vitest for `helpers/` harness packages

- Node-only harness code under **`helpers/`** (e.g. **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**, and future sibling packages) is covered by **`*.vitest.test.ts`** in each package’s **`tests/`** tree; **`yarn test:unit`** runs them as Vitest **`unit-helpers`** via [vitest.helpers.config.mts](vitest/vitest.helpers.config.mts) (file lives in repo-root **`vitest/`**, not inside **`helpers/`**). Add or extend those Vitest files when you change helper logic (env switches, temp dirs, IPC-adjacent helpers). Follow [vitest-tests.mdc](vitest-tests.mdc) for structure, comments, and **100%** **`helpers`** coverage expectations.

## Isolated `userData` reset (every spec)

- After the standard imports (see below), import **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData`** from **`app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset`** and register **`test.beforeEach(() => { resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData() })`** once per file. That removes the entire **`playwright-user-data`** directory (including **`faUserSettings.json`** and Chromium profile files) before each test so **`electron.launch`** always starts from a clean persisted profile. Path resolution matches **`appIdentity/fixAppName`** / Electron **`app.getPath('appData')`**; the folder segment is **`PLAYWRIGHT_ISOLATED_USER_DATA_DIR_NAME`** in [playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts). **Do not** import **`fixAppName`** from Node-side Playwright helpers—it imports **`electron`** and breaks test discovery; see [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset.ts). Shared Playwright harness modules live under **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**; add new cross-cutting helper packages as siblings under **`helpers/`**—keep the repo root for config, **`README`**, lockfiles, and **`scripts/`**.

## HTML report and screen recordings

- Each Electron test attaches **WebM** screen video (see [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts)) unless `FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO` is set. Open **`test-results/playwright-report/index.html`** after a run, open a test, and use **Attachments** to play or download; playable files are under **`test-results/playwright-report/data/`**.
- **Every** Playwright run **replaces** the HTML report folder. Running component tests, then E2E (or the reverse, or a repeat of either) **overwrites** the prior report—there is no merge across runs.
- Root **`yarn test:components`** / **`yarn test:e2e`** (and **`:single`** / **`:single:ci`**) use **`scripts/playwrightWithArtifactTrim.mjs`**, which deletes **`test-results/playwright-artifacts`** after the run. Raw `recordVideo` output uses a temp dir under the OS temp folder, then is attached and trimmed (see **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts`**).
- For agents: point humans to **`test-results/playwright-report/index.html`** for per-test videos; do not assume reliable analysis of raw **`.webm`** bytes without specialized tooling.

## Vue templates (hooks for locators)

Primary locators use **`data-test-locator`**; additional hooks (for example `data-test-menu-test` / `data-test-menu-any`, `data-test-tooltip-text`) are defined in **`.vue` files** — follow [vue-template-test-hooks.mdc](vue-template-test-hooks.mdc) when adding or renaming them. This rule covers the **TypeScript test files** only.

## File locations

| Kind | Path pattern |
|------|----------------|
| Component | `src/components/<Component>/tests/*.playwright.test.ts` |
| E2E | `e2e-tests/*.playwright.spec.ts` |

## Import order (top of file)

1. `import { _electron as electron } from 'playwright'`
2. `import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test'`
3. `import { extraEnvVariablesAPI } from 'app/src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/extraEnvVariablesAPI'`
4. `closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments` and `getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial` from `'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo'` (after `extraEnvVariablesAPI`)
5. `import { resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData } from 'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset'` then **`test.beforeEach(() => { resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData() })`** (see **Isolated `userData` reset** above); keep **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData`** next to other **`app/`** imports (ESLint may reorder `import type` lines after value imports).
6. Optional: types from `app/types/...`, production **`_data/`** when the spec must stay aligned with runtime (prefer a small parallel module over importing heavy feeds), shared helpers from `src/scripts/_utilities/...` (e.g. [AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/tests/AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts))

## File header — documented constants

Repeat this structure in **every** Playwright file (see [GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts), [checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts)):

1. **`extraEnvSettings`** — JSDoc: `Extra env settings to trigger component testing via Playwright` **or** `...E2E...` for e2e.
   - **Component**: `TEST_ENV: 'components'`, `COMPONENT_NAME: '<Name>'` (must match the component the harness loads), `COMPONENT_PROPS: JSON.stringify({})` or a payload built from **inline objects in this file** (e.g. `{ dataInput: menuFixture }`); **do not** import separate `tests/*.ts` files that exist only to hold fixture blobs. `TEST_ENV` triggers **`%APPDATA%/<package name>/playwright-user-data`** ([fixAppName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/fixAppName.ts), folder name in [playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts)) — not **`fantasia-archive-dev`** — so **`electron-store`** does not overlap **`quasar dev`** or packaged profiles.
   - **E2E**: `TEST_ENV: 'e2e'` only ([checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts)); same isolated **`userData`** root as component tests.

2. **`electronMainFilePath`** — JSDoc `Electron main filepath`; type `string`; value `extraEnvVariablesAPI.ELECTRON_MAIN_FILEPATH`.

3. **`faFrontendRenderTimer`** — JSDoc explaining render buffer; usually `extraEnvVariablesAPI.FA_FRONTEND_RENDER_TIMER` for components; e2e files may use a **numeric literal** (e.g. `0` or `1000`) when documented in that file.

4. **`selectorList`** — JSDoc `Object of string data selectors` (component) or `...for the e2e` (e2e). Keys are camelCase; values are the exact string stored in **`data-test-locator`** (or another `data-test-*` attribute when the test targets that attribute by name and value), visible labels for `getByText`, or a **full locator string** for rare exceptions (for example `'[role="tooltip"]'` for Quasar portaled tooltips — still centralized in `selectorList`, not hard-coded in the test body; see [DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts) `selectorList.quasarTooltip`). When a component uses several `data-test-locator` values that include dynamic suffixes (category keys, ids), keep stable entries in `selectorList` and add a small helper object or functions beside it (see the same file’s `programSettingsSelector`).

5. **Extra timers** — Only when needed (e.g. [checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts) `menuAnimationTimer = 600`; splash screen timeout local `testSplashscreenTimeout` in test).

6. **Inline fixture objects** (when needed) — typed `const` payloads (menus, props, key lists) used in assertions and in `JSON.stringify` for `COMPONENT_PROPS`, declared **in the same Playwright file** before `extraEnvSettings` or beside the test that mutates props.

## Each `test(...)`

- Precede with a **JSDoc block** describing behavior: a short baseline line (full sentence), then optional ` * - ` detail bullets. Do not wrap one long paragraph across lines mid-sentence; there is no comment line-length limit (see [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) code comments).
- **Title**: readable sentence (often starts with `Check if ...`, `Test if ...`, `Click ...`, `Open ...`).
- **Body pattern**:
  1. Optionally mutate `extraEnvSettings` (e.g. `COMPONENT_PROPS`) before launch — [FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts](src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/tests/FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts).
  2. Top-level `test(...)` callback must take `({}, testInfo)` (object destructuring is required by Playwright) so recordings can use `testInfo`. `const electronApp = await electron.launch({ env: extraEnvSettings, args: [electronMainFilePath], ...getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial(testInfo) })` — import `getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial` from `'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo'` (after `extraEnvVariablesAPI`); raw `recordVideo` files are written under an OS temp dir, then `closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments` attaches them (Playwright copies into `test-results/playwright-artifacts/.../attachments/`) and deletes the temp dir. The HTML reporter then copies bytes into `test-results/playwright-report/data/`; root `package.json` Playwright scripts run `scripts/playwrightWithArtifactTrim.mjs` afterward to remove `test-results/playwright-artifacts` so only report `data/` remains on disk. **1920×1080** (`recordVideo.size`) unless `FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO` is `'1'` or `'true'`. Each `electron.launch` must use its own `getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial(testInfo)` call (optional second argument is reserved, unused). Nested callbacks (e.g. `expect.poll`) keep `async () => { ... }` — do not add `testInfo` there.
  3. `const appWindow = await electronApp.firstWindow()` then `await installFaPlaywrightCursorMarkerIfVideoEnabled(appWindow)` (from [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts); no-op when video is off)
  4. `await appWindow.waitForTimeout(faFrontendRenderTimer)` (or 0 / other agreed wait)
  5. `// Prepare the ... locator` — use `appWindow.locator` with a template string and `selectorList` values (same pattern as [GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts)), or `getByText` with `selectorList` entries ([checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts))
  6. `// Check if ...` — `await expect(...).toHaveCount(1)` or equivalent
  7. Interactions, `waitForTimeout` for animations (often `600` ms for menus), `appWindow.evaluate` for `window.faContentBridgeAPIs...` when needed
  8. `// Close the app` then `await closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments(electronApp, testInfo)` — closes Electron, then attaches `.webm` files under `testInfo.outputDir` so the HTML report shows video links (including early returns after failure paths — [checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts))

## Locators

- **Default**: Prefer **`data-test-locator`** and other `data-test-*` hooks from `.vue` templates for every locator: `appWindow.locator(\`[data-test-locator="${selectorList.someKey}"]\`)` or `appWindow.locator(\`[${selectorList.someDataTestAttributeName}]\`)` when the entry is the full attribute name (for example `data-test-tooltip-text`). Scope under a parent `[data-test-locator="..."]` when the same static child hook appears in multiple rows (category title, setting label, etc.). Do **not** rely on BEM class names or generic Quasar classes unless there is no practical hook.
- **Exceptions** (when `data-test-locator` is impractical): stable **`id`** hooks reserved for accessibility may stay as `#...` only if the component does not mirror them with `data-test-locator` (prefer adding `data-test-locator` on the same node). **`role="*"`** and similar ARIA-driven targets are allowed when asserting portal content (for example Quasar `q-tooltip`); store the **entire** selector string in `selectorList` (for example `quasarTooltip: '[role="tooltip"]'`) and use `appWindow.locator(selectorList.quasarTooltip)` — do **not** scatter raw `[role="tooltip"]` literals in the spec. When **`locator.hover()`** does not wake a small trigger (some Quasar icons under Electron), **`page.mouse.move`** to the element’s **bounding box center** after `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` is an allowed follow-up for that interaction only ([DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts)). **E2E** tests may use **`getByText`** with strings from `selectorList` when exercising real menu or button copy ([checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts)).
- **Special menu attributes**: use exactly what the component sets, e.g. `[data-test-menu-test="..."]` and `[data-test-menu-any="..."]` ([AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/tests/AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts)).
- **Heavy tooltip suites**: duplicate tooltip body text on the trigger (for example `data-test-tooltip-text` on the help icon) so specs can assert copy without hovering every row; keep **at least one** hover + `selectorList.quasarTooltip` (or your spec’s named entry for the same full string) assertion per suite so real tooltip display stays covered ([DialogProgramSettings.vue](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/DialogProgramSettings.vue), [DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts)). Quasar **`q-tooltip`** content is portaled and delay-based under Electron: prefer **`locator.hover({ force: true })`** over raw **`page.mouse.move`**, give the configured delay plus slack, target the **last** matching **`[role="tooltip"]`** when stale nodes may linger, and wrap the hover + visibility assert in **`expect(async () => { ... }).toPass({ timeout: ... })`** to retry after moving the pointer away to dismiss.
- **WebM cursor visibility**: window capture often omits the OS pointer. After **`firstWindow()`**, call **`installFaPlaywrightCursorMarkerIfVideoEnabled(appWindow)`** from [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts) (already wired in existing Electron specs) so recordings show a red dot following synthetic **`mousemove`** positions. Set **`FA_PLAYWRIGHT_CURSOR_MARKER`** to **`0`** or **`false`** to disable; **`FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO`** skips both video and the marker.

## Shared test data

- **Do not** add a `tests/_data/` folder. **Production** structured feeds stay under the component’s **`_data/`** (e.g. menu sections, `buttonList`).
- **Playwright fixtures** (props payloads, expected key lists, golden strings) belong **inside** the same `*.playwright.test.ts` as typed **`const`** values — not in a separate **`tests/<name>.ts`** module whose only job is holding that data. Pass mount data through `COMPONENT_PROPS` / per-test `JSON.stringify` updates (see [AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/tests/AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts)).
- Avoid importing `_data` modules that pull Vite-only or heavy i18n graphs into Playwright’s Node loader when a small parallel constant list is enough (e.g. duplicate the key list next to [SocialContactButtons/_data/buttons.ts](src/components/other/SocialContactButtons/_data/buttons.ts) inside the spec with a sync comment).

## Assertions

- Prefer `await expect(locator).toHaveCount(1)` before clicks.
- Use `expect` (non-async) for plain values from `evaluate` when the codebase does ([GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts) — note existing mix of `await expect` vs `expect` on locators; **follow the immediate surrounding file** for new tests in that folder).
- Avoid `any` in selector maps, test fixtures, and helper signatures; prefer explicit interfaces/types and `unknown` plus narrowing for untyped Playwright values.

## Do not

- Do not introduce `test.describe` groups unless you migrate the whole suite — **existing files use flat `test` only**.
- Do not change `COMPONENT_NAME` / env contract without updating the component testing harness and docs.
- Do not add Playwright (or other) tests whose **system under test** is a file under any **`_data/`** folder; assert behavior through `.vue` or other non-surface that uses that data.
- For Storybook visual snapshot runs (`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`), keep these utility Playwright-harness stories excluded because they are not meaningful visual-regression targets: `layouts-componenttestinglayout--with-social-contact-single-button`, `pages-componenttesting--social-contact-single-button`. Component story **`id`** values in **`index.json`** follow **`components-<bucket>-<componentfolder>-<story>`** (for example **`components-elements-fantasiamascotimage--reading`**) when **`meta.title`** is **`Components/<bucket>/<ComponentName>`** — match that shape in **`EXCLUDED_STORY_IDS`** when excluding harness-only component previews.

## Local types extraction rule

- For Vue (`.vue`) and TypeScript (`.ts`) source files, move small file-local interfaces/type aliases into a colocated `<filename>.types.ts` file and import them back.
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
